# Final Compilation Checks

When you think the requested work is finished, do not spend time or tokens recompiling LaTeX or C++ just to verify it.
The user will check whether it compiles.

Only compile LaTeX or C++ when the user explicitly asks for it, or when runtime output is necessary to investigate a specific failure.
